{% schema %}
  {
    
    "name": "Section 4",
    "tag": "section",
    "class": "gps-607888589547635610 gps gpsil",
    "settings": [{"type":"paragraph","content":"Section design by GemPages. [Click here to start design](https://admin.shopify.com/store/sheikhashadul/apps/gempages-cro/app/shopify/edit?pageType=GP_STATIC&editorId=607864187825160759&sectionId=607888589547635610)"},{"type":"select","label":"Section Preload","id":"section_preload","options":[{"label":"On","value":"true"},{"label":"Off","value":"false"},{"label":"Off Lazy Script","value":"off_lazy_script"}],"default":"false"},{"type":"text","label":"Checksum","id":"checksum"},{"type":"html","id":"ggYaVq2q5av_text","label":"ggYaVq2q5av_text","default":"<p>The real problem isn't just the demolition crew running wild.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggK1PPOBSNT_text","label":"ggK1PPOBSNT_text","default":"<p><strong>The construction crew is exhausted.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDfWqpRTBU_text","label":"ggDfWqpRTBU_text","default":"<p><strong>They've run out of energy.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggx3NGoQExj_text","label":"ggx3NGoQExj_text","default":"<p>And this is where calcium completely fails.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg2zFUDE4Av_text","label":"gg2zFUDE4Av_text","default":"<p><strong>⚠️ The Dark Side of Calcium</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggUkYD-Waw5_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggUkYD-Waw5_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/gempages_481559650848736414-909fbcb6-962f-40b6-9283-459088503cbc.webp"},{"type":"html","id":"ggjbdzjkAKs_text","label":"ggjbdzjkAKs_text","default":"<p>Think of calcium like bricks sitting on a construction site.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguwWTKCXxy_text","label":"gguwWTKCXxy_text","default":"<p><strong>You can pile up all the bricks you want.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggX-7vMhCik_text","label":"ggX-7vMhCik_text","default":"<p><i><strong>But if your construction workers have no energy to pick them up and lay them, nothing gets built.</strong></i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggseMm8b9SO_text","label":"ggseMm8b9SO_text","default":"<p>That's exactly what's happening in your bones.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrn0YeqdxU_text","label":"ggrn0YeqdxU_text","default":"<p>All the materials in the world won't help if you have no energy...</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwQsOmpcFy_text","label":"ggwQsOmpcFy_text","default":"<p><strong>Your builders literally don't have the energy to use the calcium and vitamin D you're taking.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg8BW8Grlto_text","label":"gg8BW8Grlto_text","default":"<p>That's why you can take calcium &amp; vitamin D for years and still lose bone density.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggw27OJhNWW_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggw27OJhNWW_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/AOI_d_9M7aU46ebT5TCbp6QXpQsU2kVt.webp"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5H_LeJJO2_text","label":"gg5H_LeJJO2_text","default":"<p><strong>But here's the kicker:</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggahzKgzxOj_text","label":"ggahzKgzxOj_text","default":"<p>When your body has too much calcium... it begins to build up in the blood.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggih5RT0a13_text","label":"ggih5RT0a13_text","default":"<p><i>It can lead to deposits in the walls of your arteries, creating calcified blockages which strain your kidneys.</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggLCdxf_X37_text","label":"ggLCdxf_X37_text","default":"<p>For some, that ends in kidney stones.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5BqC3CDaR_text","label":"gg5BqC3CDaR_text","default":"<p><strong>For others… it ends in something far worse.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggnCTwVJD3Q_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggnCTwVJD3Q_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/Gemini_Generated_Image_prhxxpprhxxpprhx.webp"},{"type":"html","id":"ggzwfbjHOYY_text","label":"ggzwfbjHOYY_text","default":"<p><strong>Later Dr. Chen wrote something that made me want to cry:</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggJrUZ49ox-_text","label":"ggJrUZ49ox-_text","default":"<p><i>\"For decades, we told women the problem was calcium deficiency. We were wrong. The problem is cellular energy deficiency.\"</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3c7rXHIA9_text","label":"gg3c7rXHIA9_text","default":"<p>I sat at my kitchen table at 2 AM, reading this. And I started crying.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggMuibq8iiM_text","label":"ggMuibq8iiM_text","default":"<p>Not sad tears. Angry tears.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwvAH1Ckij_text","label":"ggwvAH1Ckij_text","default":"<p><strong>How many years had I wasted? How much bone density had I lost that I could have saved?</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggkpCB1iB7-_text","label":"ggkpCB1iB7-_text","default":"<p>But then Dr. Chen shared something that gave me hope for the first time in weeks.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggDK2V330uo_text","label":"ggDK2V330uo_text","default":"<p><strong>The Discovery That Changed Everything</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrAK7I_Ntz_text","label":"ggrAK7I_Ntz_text","default":"<p>Dr. Chen's research led him to a small group of islands in Japan.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguWlg5VN2O_text","label":"gguWlg5VN2O_text","default":"<p><strong>Okinawa.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggwjvn_EbHT_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"ggwjvn_EbHT_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/gempages_481559650848736414-4d7ec6a2-cdb6-4fe0-ac2e-4adaa3b884db.webp"},{"type":"html","id":"ggaY1Nxymqz_text","label":"ggaY1Nxymqz_text","default":"<p>Women there stay strong into their 70s and 80s. They don't live in fear of fractures.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggVJ-LLabj6_text","label":"ggVJ-LLabj6_text","default":"<p>Scientists wanted to know why.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gglMVQ0P-my_text","label":"gglMVQ0P-my_text","default":"<p>What they found was shocking:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg1VInSjAqI_text","label":"gg1VInSjAqI_text","default":"<p><strong>Okinawan women naturally maintain up to 45% higher levels of this molecule called NAD+ their entire lives.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggs8Y1PGWfq_text","label":"ggs8Y1PGWfq_text","default":"<p>NAD+ is an essential coenzyme found in every living cell, that plays a crucial role in cellular function.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg3QPAlfDu1_text","label":"gg3QPAlfDu1_text","default":"<p>Think of it like the battery that powers all trillion cells in your body.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcIser-BVu_text","label":"ggcIser-BVu_text","default":"<p>And as you get older your bone-building cells need massive amounts of it to do their job.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggzp-cwenN__text","label":"ggzp-cwenN__text","default":"<p><strong>But after age 40, your NAD+ levels drop by up to 50%.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg5AXhDAlQd_srcSet_desktop_src","label":"gg5AXhDAlQd_srcSet_desktop_src","default":"https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0993/4700/5732/files/gempages_481559650848736414-6f391a7f-698d-4d6b-944e-e2f18276f959.webp"},{"type":"html","id":"ggi_4MBgF5l_text","label":"ggi_4MBgF5l_text","default":"<p><strong>It turns out that the Okinawan women have figured out the secret.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gggfmV6ftsQ_text","label":"gggfmV6ftsQ_text","default":"<p>They eat foods loaded with NAD+, purple sweet potatoes, fermented soybeans, and fresh fish.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggIuzM6Lj3__text","label":"ggIuzM6Lj3__text","default":"<p>Their bone-building cells stay charged, which means their bones stay strong.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gguRRAufuRL_text","label":"gguRRAufuRL_text","default":"<p>They also live in cleaner environments with less pollution. Less oxidative stress draining their cellular energy.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggWXp_gylzf_text","label":"ggWXp_gylzf_text","default":"<p>The result? 40% fewer hip fractures than American women. But here's the problem for the rest of us.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggkoiGyV_k__text","label":"ggkoiGyV_k__text","default":"<p><strong>We can't eat like Okinawans.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg_WP8PApQk_text","label":"gg_WP8PApQk_text","default":"<p>Our food supply is polluted with pesticides and toxins. Our stress is higher. Our air quality is worse.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggh32VUcwLQ_text","label":"ggh32VUcwLQ_text","default":"<p><strong>Our NAD+ gets drained faster than ever before.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggkUqY-sByD_text","label":"ggkUqY-sByD_text","default":"<p>Dr. Chen realized something important:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggHpcr1IMiU_text","label":"ggHpcr1IMiU_text","default":"<p><strong>The result? 40% fewer hip fractures than American women.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggvmhSg1GpI_text","label":"ggvmhSg1GpI_text","default":"<p>But here's the problem for the rest of us.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg4cFwssT7x_text","label":"gg4cFwssT7x_text","default":"<p><strong>We can't eat live like Okinawans.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggssFmSogO__text","label":"ggssFmSogO__text","default":"<p>Our food supply is polluted with pesticides and toxins. Our stress is higher. Our air quality is worse.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggVz71yh-uX_text","label":"ggVz71yh-uX_text","default":"<p><strong>Our NAD+ gets drained faster than ever before.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggSPD1Z0wjI_text","label":"ggSPD1Z0wjI_text","default":"<p>Dr. Chen realized something important:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggcU39R_nFq_text","label":"ggcU39R_nFq_text","default":"<p><strong>If we could restore NAD+ levels directly, we could give the bone-building cells the energy they desperately need.</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggTVcTbf1s3_text","label":"ggTVcTbf1s3_text","default":"<p>And that's exactly why Big Pharma keeps pushing drugs that never fix the real problem.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"gg9W7VMrxmy_text","label":"gg9W7VMrxmy_text","default":"<p>They profit off keeping women trapped on medications that only slow damage, never heal it.</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggt7_gQtCxx_text","label":"ggt7_gQtCxx_text","default":"<p><strong>Why Drugs Will Never Fix The Real Problem</strong></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggrXP6UgwF6_text","label":"ggrXP6UgwF6_text","default":"<p>Dr. Chen explained something that finally made sense of why antiresorptive drugs have such terrible track records:</p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggOIPtBGrH4_text","label":"ggOIPtBGrH4_text","default":"<p><i>\"Bisphosphonates like Fosamax slow bone loss by stopping your demolition crew. But they do nothing to build new bone.\"</i></p>"},{"type":"html","id":"ggKL5BF9XlR_text","label":"ggKL5BF9XlR_text","default":"<p><i>\"Worse, long-term use &nbsp;can create \"frozen bone\" that becomes brittle. That's why women on these drugs for years still fracture.\"</i></p>"}],
    "blocks": [{"type": "@app"}],
    "locales": {}
  }
